						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. 3) set up in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>Chōḻa-mahārāja, circa 9th century.</p>						

						<p>This record refers to <hi rend="bold">Chōḻa-mahārāja</hi> as ruling <hi rend="bold">Pulināḍu-60</hi> division and to the great victory of Kalliyaṇṇa, son-in-law of Būdali Ponnayya and son of Pallaya-gāmuṇḍa in a cattle-raid at Maṅgala.</p>						

						</summary>
